h%20customer%20confrontations%20with%20the%20mindset%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20blame%20the%20customer.%20Blame%20the%20machine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20policy%20is%20to%20take%20the%20item%20away%20from%20them%20and%20tell%20them%20something%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20think%20the%20machine%20didn't%20scan%20it.'%20And%20if%20they%20don't%20want%20it%2C%20then%20we%20take%20it%20away.%20If%20they%20do%20want%20it%2C%20we%20scan%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20employee%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20at%20Walmart%20locations%20for%20over%20two%20years%2C%20said%20the%20self-checkout%20technology%20caught%20many%20customers%20off%20guard%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20when%20they%20saw%20that%20the%20registers%20flagged%20them%20and%20then%20played%20back%20a%20video%20on%20the%20machine's%20screen%20showing%20them%20scanning%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20self-checkout%20technology%20%26quot%3Bfeels%20more%20confrontational%20than%20it%20was%20before%20because%20it's%20right%20there%20%E2%80%94%20the%20evidence%20is%20right%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20video%2C%20which%20is%20visible%20to%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20approaches%20customers%20flagged%20by%20the%20self-checkout%20machines%2C%20she%20said%2C%20they%20often%20act%20defensive%20or%20confused.%20She%20added%20that%20Walmart%20didn't%20train%20her%20on%20%26quot%3Bde-escalation%20tactics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20shopper%20pushes%20a%20cart%20through%20the%20parking%20lot%20of%20a%20Walmart%20in%20Wilmington%2C%20Delaware.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64678492cd3a9c0019185627%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWalmart%20says%20associates%20are%20trained%20so%20that%20%26quot%3Bour%20customers%20have%20a%20safe%20and%20enjoyable%20shopping%20experience.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESAMUEL%20CORUM%2FAFP%20