2012%20weeks%20of%20unpaid%20leave%2C%20I%20wasn't%20eligible%20for%20that.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20those%C2%A0non-negotiable%20parts%20of%20American%20work%20culture%20that%20I%20felt%20I%20had%20to%C2%A0accept.%C2%A0I%20only%20had%20four%20weeks%20of%20paid%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20eventually%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20move%20to%20Europe%20%E2%80%94%20so%20with%20the%20arrival%20of%20my%20second%20and%20third%20sons%2C%20I%C2%A0was%20able%20to%20bask%20in%20the%20luxury%20of%20nine%20months%20of%20maternity%20leave.%20I%C2%A0even%20managed%20to%20extend%20my%20time%20off%20while%20keeping%20my%20job%20secure%20for%20nearly%C2%A0two%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20differences%20that%20I%20found%20between%20my%20experiences%20of%20pregnancy%20and%20maternity%20leave%20in%20the%20US%20versus%20Europe%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20which%20were%20surprising%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaternity%20leave%20and%20parenting%20in%20the%20US%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere's%20pressure%20to%20start%20a%20family%20before%20age%2030%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20soon%20as%20you%20get%20married%20or%20anywhere%20close%20to%2030%2C%20you'll%20hear%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%20when%20are%20you%20going%20to%20have%20a%20baby%3F%26quot%3B%20from%20family%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20colleagues.%20My%20community%20was%20no%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20felt%20a%20lack%20of%20support%20after%20the%20baby%20arrived%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20son%20arrived%20after%20a%20grueling%20home%20water%20birth%20that%20lasted%20nearly%20two%20full%20days%2C%20I%20suddenly%20felt%20alone%20and%20adrift.%20The%20midwives%20packed%20up%20their%20birthing%20equipment%2C%20my%20family%20returned%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20and%20we%20were%20left%20alone%20to%20figure%20things%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20I%20remember%20these%20early%20days%20of%20our%20little%20family%20with%20nostalgia%20%E2%80%94%20and%20exhaustion.%20My%20husband's%20family%20is%20in%20Europe%2C%20and%20we%20took%20advantage%20of%20his%20mother's%20nursing%20experience%20and%20nine-hour%20time%20difference%20for%20advice%20at%20any%20hour%20of%20the%20day.%20She%20guided%20us%20through%20that%20first%20year%20from%20afar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20was%20pressure%20to%20get%20back%20to%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20experience%20in%20the%20workforce%20was%20similar%20%E2%80%94%20plenty%20of%20excitement%20before%20the%20baby%20was%20born%2C%20but%20afterward%20the%20focus%20was%20%26quot%3BWhen%20will%20you%20return%20to%20the%20office%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BIt's%20time%20to%20get%20back%20to%20business.%26quot%3B%20The%20time%20for%20consideration%20and%20adjustments%20for%20me%20and%20my%20child%20ended%20abruptly%20and%20unexpectedly.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20employer%20allowed%20me%20to%20work%20remotely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20making%20a%20good%20salary%20as%20an%20account%20executive%2C%20and%20when%20my%20employer%20agreed%20to%20let%20me%20work%20from%20home%2C%20this%20allowed%20me%C2%A0to%20prioritize%20nursing%20and%20bonding%20with%20my%20newborn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20husband%20stayed%20home%20with%20our%20son%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20start%20a%20family%20in%20the%20US%2C%20we%20made%20the%20decision%20for%20him%20to%20stay%20home%20with%20our%20son%20during%C2%A0this%20crucial%20time%2C%20rather%20than%20put%20our%20baby%20in%20daycare%20or%20hire%20a%20nanny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20jobs%20are%20harder%20to%20manage%20leave%20on%20than%20others%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20account%20executive%2C%20I%20found%20that%20sales%20positions%20are%20especially%20difficult%20to%20take%20family%20leave%20with%20because%20someone%20needs%20to%20take%20over%20your%20book%20of%20business%20while%20you%20are%20on%20leave.%20Once%20you%20come%20back%2C%20they%20often%20don't%20want%20to%20give%20back%20the%20accounts%20they've%20been%20covering%20and%20earning%20the%20commission%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20whether%20or%20not%20this%20happens%20depends%20on%20your%20relationship%20with%20your%20colleagues%20and%20how%20you've%20covered%20for%20them%20in%20the%20past.%20I%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20excellent%20colleagues%20whom%20I'd%20helped%20many%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20to%20return%20to%20work%20sooner%20than%20I%20wanted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20had%20four%20weeks%20of%20paid%20leave%2C%20and%20my%20employer%20didn't%20have%20to%20hold%20my%20job%20for%20more%20than%20six%20weeks.%20With%20financial%20pressures%20weighing%20our%20new%20family%20down%2C%20I%20reluctantly%20returned%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20new%20mom%2C%20I'd%20barely%20established%20a%20nursing%20routine%2C%20and%20I%20was%20still%20struggling%20with%20sleep%2C%20anxiety%2C%20and%20the%20desire%20to%20hold%20and%20snuggle%20my%20newborn.%20I%20know%20I%20was%20luckier%20than%20most%2C%20but%20for%20me%2C%20four%20weeks%20wasn't%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wanted%20a%20longer%20leave%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20watched%20my%20son%20experience%20those%20precious%20firsts%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0tasting%20different%20foods%2C%20chasing%20after%20our%20cats%2C%20and%20uttering%20adorable%20baby%20sounds%20%E2%80%94%20I%20couldn't%20help%20but%20feel%20a%20deep%20yearning%20for%20more%C2%A0time%20with%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20longing%20led%20us%20to%20explore%20opportunities%20abroad%2C%20looking%20for%20businesses%C2%A0to%20invest%20in%20that%20would%20reduce%20our%20financial%20burden%20and%20give%20us%20more%C2%A0freedom%20to%20cherish%20these%20precious%20moments.%C2%A0It%20was%20when%20we%20were%20visiting%20Europe%20%E2%80%94%20just%20six%20weeks%20after%20our%20baby%20was%20born%20%E2%80%94%20that%20we%20started%20to%20formulate%20our%20move%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaternity%20leave%20and%20parenting%20in%20Europe%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20have%20more%20time%20for%20children%20and%20family%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20felt%20a%20definitive%20shift%20while%20in%20Europe%20visiting%20my%20husband's%20family.%20Everyone%20was%20eager%20to%20actually%20spend%20time%20with%20us%20and%20our%20son.%20They%20were%20not%20too%20busy%20for%20babysitting%20or%20playing%3B%20they%20always%20had%20time.%20When%20we%20did%20make%20the%20move%20to%20Europe%2C%20things%20continued%20in%20much%20the%20same%20way.%20Spending%20time%20with%20our%20son%20was%20a%20constant%20priority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20understand%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20family%20in%20Europe%2C%20and%20it's%20prioritized.%20European%20culture%20is%20more%20centered%20on%20family%2C%20and%20life%20runs%20at%20a%20slower%20pace.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20felt%20more%20supported%20by%20colleagues%20in%20Europe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20working%20in%20Europe%2C%20I%20moved%20into%20a%20teaching%20position.%20There%20were%20days%20when%20I%20took%20my%20then%20three-year-old%20son%20to%20preschool%20and%20he%20refused%20to%20let%20me%20go.%20I%20took%20him%20to%20class%20for%20a%20while%20and%20the%20only%20reaction%20was%20one%20of%20adoration%20and%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20had%20our%20second%20son%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20leave%20work%20a%20month%20before%20my%20due%20date%20to%20focus%20on%20getting%20ready%20for%20the%20further%20expansion%20of%20our%20family.%20Colleagues%20frequently%20called%20to%20check%20up%20on%20me%2C%20as%20did%20my%20principal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETeachers%20have%20unique%20issues%20when%20dealing%20with%20maternity%20leave%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20working%20as%20a%20teacher%20in%20Europe%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20although%20schools%20are%20accustomed%20to%20giving%20maternity%20leave%2C%20they%20need%20to%20also%20deal%20with%20a%20new%20hire%20who%20they%20then%20need%20to%20find%20a%20job%20for%20once%20the%20teacher%20on%20leave%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20usually%20happens%20is%20that%20teacher%20will%20be%20needed%20in%20another%20classroom%20because%20someone%20else%20will%20go%20on%20leave%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20always%20work%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%20at%20my%20former%20school%2C%20the%20gym%20teacher%20is%20teaching%20the%20music%20class%20until%20the%20music%20teacher%20returns%20from%20leave%20because%20they%20couldn't%20find%20a%20suitable%20replacement%20for%20one%20semester%20only.%20But%20if%20there's%20a%20standard%20of%20maternity%20leave%20throughout%20the%20country%20and%20company%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20much%20easier%20to%20find%20coverage%20for%20those%20nine%20or%20more%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20got%20a%20longer%20leave%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20still%20was%20too%20short%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20we%20made%20the%20move%20to%20Europe%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20enjoy%20a%20long%20maternity%20leave%20with%20my%20two%20younger%20sons%2C%20and%20I%20found%20even%20nine%20months%20isn't%20enough%20time.%20Nine%20months%20is%20a%20developmental%20milestone%20when%20your%20child%20is%20starting%20to%20really%20get%20interesting%20and%20fun%2C%20crawling%20and%20trying%20to%20talk%20and%20getting%20into%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20able%20to%20take%20additional%20time%20off%20after%20my%20leave%20ended%20plus%20had%20job%20security%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20difference%20with%20taking%20maternity%20leave%20from%20my%20job%20in%20Europe%20versus%20the%20US%20was%20that%20in%20Europe%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20extend%20my%20leave%20and%20still%20keep%20my%20job%20secure.%20After%20my%20second%20son%20was%20born%20in%20Europe%2C%20I%20continued%20to%20feel%20the%20support%20and%20understanding%20of%20those%20surrounding%20us.%C2%A