%20criticise%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%20and%20promote%20Chinese%20propaganda.%20The%20portal%20has%20denied%20these%20allegations%20and%20said%20in%20court%20that%20they%20did%20not%20receive%20even%20a%20penny%20from%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20have%20also%20challenged%20the%20FIR%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gedela%20had%20reserved%20judgment%20in%20the%20matter%20on%20October%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArguing%20for%20Purkayastha%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%20had%20said%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20were%20not%20provided%20at%20the%20time%20of%20arrest%20or%20even%20in%20the%20remand%20order%2C%20thus%20going%20against%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20on%20arrests.%20The%20editor%20was%20also%20not%20allowed%20to%20have%20a%20lawyer%20of%20his%20choice%20present%20during%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20remand%20order%2C%20it%20was%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22NewsClick%20Case%3A%20Do%20Allegations%20Justify%20Invoking%20of%20UAPA%3F%20Legal%20Experts%20Weigh%20In.%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnewsclick-case-allegations-uapa-legal-experts%5C%22%3ENewsClick%20Case%3A%20Do%20Allegations%20Justify%20Invoking%20of%20UAPA%3F%20Legal%20Experts%20Weigh%20In.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESibal%20also%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20a%20rupee%2C%20not%20a%20penny%E2%80%9D%20had%20come%20from%20China%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20Purkayastha.%20The%20Delhi%20Police%20FIR%20%E2%80%93%20which%20casts%20a%20wide%20net%2C%20ranging%20from%20Chinese%20phone%20producers%20to%20lawyers%20to%20protesting%20farmers%20%E2%80%93%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20portal%20received%20Chinese%20government%20funding%20to%20spread%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20Sibal%20and%20senior%20advocate%20Dayan%20Krishnan%2C%20appearing%20for%20Purkayastha%2C%20referred%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20recent%20judgment%20in%20the%20case%20of%20%3Cem%3EPankaj%20Bansal%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20court%20had%20said%20that%20a%20written%20copy%20of%20the%20grounds%20for%20arrest%20must%20be%20provided%20to%20an%20accused%20at%20the%20time%20of%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20magistrate%20who%20sent%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20to%20seven%20days%20police%20remand%20did%20not%20ensure%20that%20this%20had%20been%20followed%2C%20and%20also%20did%20not%20check%20if%20the%20accused%20had%20access%20to%20their%20lawyers%2C%20Krishnan%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESolicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20state%2C%20said%20that%20petitioners%20had%20been%20told%20about%20the%20grounds%20for%20arrest.%20He%20argued%20that%20under%20UAPA%20guidelines%2C%20a%20written%20copy%20is%20not%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Justice%20Gedela%20said%20he%20did%20not%20find%20any%20merit%20in%20the%20petitions%20challenging%20remand%20and%20was%20hence%20dismissing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20are%20presently%20in%20judicial%20custody%20until%20October%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697183826000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07130338%2FUntitled-design-2021-02-10T154651.122.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-hc-dismisses-newsclick-editor-hr-heads-pleas-challenging-remand-order%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justice%20Gedela%20said%20he%20did%20not%20find%20any%20merit%20in%20the%20petitions%20challenging%20remand%20and%20was%20hence%20dismissing%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-hc-dismisses-newsclick-editor-hr-heads-pleas-challenging-remand-order%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IND%20vs%20PAK%3A%20The%20heartstopping%20finishes%