dernized-saree-and-halter-neck-blouse%2Fphotostory%2F104375399.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104375399.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ETamannaah%20Bhatia%20looks%20gorgeous%20in%20neon%20saree%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20obsessed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Ftamannaah-bhatia-is-a-vision-to-behold-in-modernized-saree-and-halter-neck-blouse%2Fphotostory%2F104375399.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bilkis%20Bano%20Convicts%20Remission%3A%20%E2%80%98Reform%20Is%20an%20Opportunity%2C%20Not%20a%20Right%E2%80%99%2C%26nbsp%3BSC%20Told%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F22114407%2Fsupreme-court.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20division%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%2C%20on%20Thursday%2C%20October%2012%2C%20concluded%20hearing%20arguments%20in%20the%20challenges%20to%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20remission%20order%20to%20prematurely%20release%2011%20convicts%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20gang%20rape%20case%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2022%2F38741%2F38741_2022_13_8_47676_Order_12-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereserved%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20its%20judgment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBano%20listened%20to%20the%20arguments%20of%20the%20counsel%20in%20the%20court%20remotely.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20case%20has%20its%20origins%20in%20the%20erroneous%20order%20passed%20by%20another%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20court%20on%20May%2013%2C%202022.%C2%A0%20In%20this%20order%2C%20Justices%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAjay%20Rastogi%20and%20Vikram%20Nath%20held%20that%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20remission%20policy%20of%201992%20would%20be%20applicable%20since%20that%20was%20the%20policy%20in%20place%20at%20the%20time%20of%20conviction.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Rastogi-Nath%20bench%20also%20held%20that%20the%20appropriate%20government%20to%20decide%20the%20remission%20question%20was%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20because%20the%20case%20was%20transferred%20to%20Maharashtra%20for%20a%20limited%20purpose%2C%20that%20is%2C%20trial%20of%20the%20case.%20And%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20trial%20and%20the%20prisoners%20being%20convicted%2C%20the%20case%20stood%20transferred%20to%20the%20state%20where%20the%20crime%20was%20committed%2C%20the%20bench%20had%20concluded.%C2%A0%20Therefore%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20Gujarat%20would%20remain%20the%20appropriate%20government%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20using%20remission%20or%20suspension%20powers%20under%20Section%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1464506%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3D(1)%2520When%2520any%2520person%2520has%2Cwhich%2520he%2520has%2520been%2520sentenced.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E432(7)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC).%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Indira%20Jaising%2C%20counsel%20for%20one%20of%20the%20interveners%20before%20the%20court%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20erroneously%20quashed%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20order%20directing%20the%20convicts%20to%20approach%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%20as%20it%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Cappropriate%E2%80%9D%20government%20under%20the%20law%20to%20decide%20the%20issue.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20of%20the%20convict%2C%20Radheshyam%20Bhagwandas%20Shah%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ealias%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Lala%20Vakil%2C%20was%20under%20Article%2032%20and%20not%20a%20Special%20Leave%20Petition%2C%20as%20no%20writ%20could%20lie%20against%20a%20judicial%20order%2C%20she%20underlined.%20She%20relied%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1643138%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENaresh%20Shridhar%20Mirajkar%20vs%20State%20of%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E(1966)%20to%20support%20this%20contention.%20She%20described%20this%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfraud%E2%80%9D%20played%20on%20the%20court%20by%20the%20convict-petitioner%2C%20who%20had%20filed%20a%20writ%20petition%20instead%20of%20an%20SLP%20in%20order%20to%20assail%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%20Besides%2C%20she%20said%20there%20was%20no%20prayer%20in%20the%20writ%20petition%20to%20set%20aside%20the%202019%20judgment%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20declaring%20Mahrashtra%20as%20the%20appropriate%20government%20to%20decide%20the%20remission%20of%20convicts%20in%20this%20case.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecondly%2C%20Jaising%20also%20assailed%20the%20May%2013%2C%202022%20order%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20because%20it%20was%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20per%20incuriam.%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20court%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efailed%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20relevant%20statutory%20provisions%20or%20precedents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20division%20bench%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ERadheshyam%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%20ignored%20the%20principle%20laid%20down%20by%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESriharan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ecase%20earlier.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20interpreting%20Section%20432(7)%20of%20the%20CrPC%2C%20the%20constitution%20bench%20held%20that%20even%20if%20an%20offence%20is%20committed%20in%20State%20A%20and%20the%20trial%20takes%20place%20and%20the%20sentence%20is%20passed%20in%20State%20B%2C%20it%20is%20the%20latter%20State%20which%20shall%20be%20the%20appropriate%20government.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20the%20decision%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EV.%20Sriharan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20known%20to%20the%20division%20bench%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ERadheshyam%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%20it%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fgujarat-governments-decision-to-remit-sentences-of-convicts-in-bilkis-bano-case-flies-in-the-face-of-legal-precedents%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enowhere%20cared%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20explain%20why%20the%20said%20decision%20was%20inapplicable%20to%20this%20case.%20The%20trial%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20case%20was%20held%20in%20Maharashtra%20and%20the%20appeals%20against%20the%20trial%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20were%20also%20heard%20by%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court.%20Although%20as%20a%20general%20proposition%2C%20a%20previous%20coordinate%20bench%E2%80%99s%20decision%20is%20binding%20on%20the%20division%20bench%2C%20Jaising%20argued%20that%20in%20this%20case%2C%20it%20is%20not%2C%20because%20it%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eper%20incuriam.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThird%2C%20Jaising%20said%20the%20premeditated%20motive%20of%20the%20convict%20has%20a%20major%20role%20to%20play%20in%20sentencing%20and%20remission.%20In%20a%20nutshell%2C%20she%20claimed%20the%20question%20before%20the%20court%20has%20a%20bearing%20on%20its%20conscience%20as%20well%20as%20that%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cball%20is%20in%20your%20court%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECounsel%20Vrinda%20Grover%2C%20appearing%20for%20another%20intervenor%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20she%20is%20neither%20opposing%20the%20power%20of%20remission%20nor%20the%20opportunity%20of%20reform%20provided%20to%20the%20conflicts.%20What%20is%20under%20challenge%20is%20the%20mala%20fide%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20remission%20was%20granted%20to%20the%20convicts%2C%20she%20told%20the%20bench.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%20the%20right%20question%20to%20ask%20while%20exercising%20the%20power%20of%20remission%20is%20about%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20crime%2C%20and%20the%20public%20welfare%20involved%2C%20as%20it%20is%20a%20noble%20power%20given%20to%20the%20state.%20%E2%80%9CDoes%20the%20offence%20affect%20the%20society%20at%20large%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGrover%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20convicts%20could%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20prison%2C%20and%20given%20a%20fresh%20opportunity%20to%20apply%20for%20remission%20before%20the%20appropriate%20government%20(that%20is%2C%20Maharashtra)%2C%20which%20would%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20consider%20their%20applications%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20crime%20committed%2C%20public%20welfare%2C%20and%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20presiding%20judge%2C%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECounsel%20Aparna%20Bhat%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20another%20intervenor%2C%20assailed%20the%20complete%20absence%20of%20application%20of%20mind%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20state%20government%20while%20remitting%20the%20sentence%20of%20the%20convicts.%C2%A0%20She%20claimed%20that%20it%20is%20extremely%20perverse%20to%20say%20that%20convicts%20have%20a%20right%20to%20reform.%20Instead%2C%20the%20convicts%20have%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20they%20have%20reformed%20in%20order%20to%20claim%20remission%2C%20she%20submitted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Nizam%20Pasha%20highlighted%20that%20the%20remission%20decision%20of%20the%20state%20government%20ignored%20the%20heinous%20nature%20of%20the%20crime.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-rapists-are-brahmins-have-good-values-says-bjp-mla-who-sat-on-panel-that-freed-convicts%5C%22%3EBilkis%20Rapists%20Are%20%E2%80%98Brahmins%2C%20Have%20Good%20Values%2C%E2%80%99%20Says%20BJP%20MLA%20Who%20Sat%20on%20Panel%20That%20Freed%20Convicts%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EOther%20arguments%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Shobha%20Gupta%2C%20appearing%20for%20Bano%2C%20had%20earlier%20submitted%20to%20the%20bench%20that%20the%20punishment%20should%20be%20proportional%20to%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20crime%2C%20which%20in%20this%20case%2C%20involved%2014%20murders%20and%20three%20gang-rapes.%20Considering%20the%20brutality%20and%20the%20religious%20hatred%20which%20was%20the%20motive%2C%20the%20convicts%20do%20not%20deserve%20remission%2C%20she%20argued.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Gujarat%20government%2C%20through%20the%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20S.V.%20Raju%2C%20submitted%20that%20it%20was%20bound%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20previous%20order%20directing%20it%20to%20consider%20remission%20applications%20of%20the%20convicts%20under%20the%201992%20policy%20which%20was%20in%20force%20at%20the%20time%20of%20their%20conviction.%20This%20policy%20was%20only%20superseded%20in%202014%2C%20making%20them%20ineligible%20to%20apply%20for%20remission%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20crime%20committed%20by%20them%20was%20heinous.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20the%20state%20government%20relied%20on%20the%20reformative%20theory%20of%20punishment%20to%20submit%20that%20those%20found%20to%20have%20committed%20heinous%20crimes%20too%20deserved%20to%20reform%20themselves%20and%20show%20remorse%20after%20serving%20their%20sentences.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESiddharth%20Luthra%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%2C%20said%20none%20of%20the%20courts%20finding%20them%20guilty%20had%20deprived%20them%20the%20opportunity%20to%20apply%20for%20remission%20of%20their%20sentences.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20non-payment%20of%20fines%20by%20the%20convicts%20was%20construed%20by%20the%20intervenors%20as%20an%20indication%20of%20absence%20of%20remorse%2C%20which%20cast%20doubts%20on%20their%20claim%20that%20they%20are%20entitled%20to%20reform.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697178558000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F22114407%2Fsupreme-court.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbilkis-bano-convicts-remission-supreme-court-reserve-order%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20reserved%20its%20judgment%20in%20the%20pleas%20against%20remission%20granted%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20to%2011%20convicts%20sentenced%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20for%20crimes%20committed%20during%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20pogrom.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbilkis-bano-convicts-remission-supreme-court-reserve-order%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nagaland%20BJP%20Leader%20Invites%20Criticism%2C%20Ridicule%20for%20Calling%20Israel%20a%20'Christian%20Country'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13114609%2F311614350_124487373729843_4564250408685590766_n.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20hurry%20to%20get%20on%20to%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20bandwagon%20against%20opposition%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20statement%20on%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%2C%20Nagaland%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20and%20a%20top%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20leader%20from%20the%20Northeast%2C%20Yanthungo%20Patton%2C%20seemed%20to%20have%20only%20flaunted%20his%20ignorance%20about%20the%20country%20he%20was%20siding%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindutva%20brigade%20came%20out%20in%20full%20support%20of%20Israel%20and%20termed%20Hamas%20(and%20also%20all%20of%20Palestine%2C%20civilians%20included)%20a%20%E2%80%98terrorist%E2%80%99%20on%20social%20media%20platforms%20in%20tandem%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20all-out%20support%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENortheast%20BJP%20leaders%20like%20Assam%20chief%20minister%20Himanta%20Biswa%20Sarma%20soon%20jumped%20on%20to%20X%20to%20follow%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20line.%20Patton%20seemed%20to%20have%20thought%20of%20adding%20an%20extra%20angle%20to%20grab%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Christian-majority%20population%20of%20his%20state.%20In%20an%20upload%20on%20X%2C%20he%20accused%20the%20Congress%20of%20being%20%E2%80%9Canti-Christian%E2%80%9D%20by%20claiming%20that%20Israel%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9CChristian%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCongress%20party%20is%20anti-Christian%20party.%20PM%20Modi%20stood%20in%20solidarity%20with%20a%20Christian%20country%20%E2%80%93%20Israel%2C%20but%20Congress%20party%20instead%20of%20supporting%20Israel%20supports%20terrorist%20Hamas.%20So%20Congress%20Party%20is%20anti-Christian%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20Patton%2C%20an%20MLA%20from%20the%20Christian-majority%20Tyui%20assembly%20constituency%2C%20was%20trolled%20for%20not%20knowing%20that%20Israel%20is%20a%20Jewish%20state%20and%20yet%20commenting%20on%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20face-off.%20It%20pushed%20him%20to%20delete%20the%20text%2C%20but%20not%20before%20it%20went%20viral%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2013%20morning%2C%20Patton%20put%20out%20another%20post%20on%20X%20which%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20context%20of%20the%20ongoing%20Israel-Hamas%20war%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20religious%20compositions%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20that%20we%2C%20as%20people%20of%20the%20world%2C%20never%20side%20with%20terror%20and%20terrorists.%20India%20has%20been%20clear%20about%20it%20and%20the%20stance%20has%20been%20strongly%20echoed%20by%20our%20honourable%20Prime%20Minister%20Shri%20Narendra%20Modi%20ji.%20However%2C%20if%20any%20individual%20or%20political%20party%20side%20with%20terror%2C%20it%20raises%20serious%20questions%20about%20their%20commitment%20to%20well-being%20of%20people%20across%20world%20and%20global%20peace.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20by%20the%20time%20the%20Nagaland%20BJP%20leader%20came%20up%20with%20the%20new%20statement%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20altered%20its%20initial%20position%20on%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict.%20Like%20the%20Congress%20in%20its%20statement%20had%20called%20for%20shunning%20violence%20and%20reiterated%20India%E2%80%99s%20longstanding%20Palestine%20policy%20by%20referring%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Clegitimate%20aspirations%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-reminds-of-obligation-to-observe-international-humanitarian-law-reiterates-support-for-palestinian-state%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20too%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20October%2012%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20policy%20in%20this%20regard%20(a%20Palestinian%20state)%20has%20been%20long-standing%20and%20consistent.%20India%20has%20always%20advocated%20resumption%20of%20direct%20negotiations%20towards%20establishing%20a%20sovereign%2C%20independent%20and%20viable%20State%20of%20Palestine%20living%20within%20secure%20and%20recognized%20borders%2C%20side%20by%20side%20at%20peace%20with%20Israel.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697178080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13114609%2F311614350_124487373729843_4564250408685590766_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnagaland-bjp-leader-invites-criticism-ridicule-for-calling-israel-a-christian-country%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Deputy%2