22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F12%2Fisrael-white-phosphorus-used-gaza-lebanon%5C%22%3Erelentlessly%20bombed%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20not%20even%20making%20a%20token%20appeal%20for%20restraint%20and%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20he%20negated%20the%20vision%20of%20support%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20articulated%20by%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20and%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20when%20India%20was%20fighting%20for%20freedom.%20That%20vision%20was%20articulated%20by%20successive%20prime%20ministers%20from%20Nehru%20to%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20interview%20published%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EJewish%20Chronicle%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0on%20October%202%2C%201931%2C%20Gandhi%20famously%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CZionism%20meaning%20reoccupation%20of%20Palestine%20has%20no%20attraction%20for%20me%E2%80%A6%20I%20can%20understand%20the%20longing%20of%20a%20Jew%20to%20return%20to%20Palestine%2C%20and%20he%20can%20do%20so%20if%20he%20can%20without%20the%20help%20of%20bayonets%2C%20whether%20his%20own%20or%20those%20of%20Britain.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeven%20years%20later%20on%20November%2026%2C%201938%20he%20emphatically%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EHarijan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CPalestine%20belongs%20to%20the%20Arabs%20in%20the%20same%20sense%20that%20England%20belongs%20to%20the%20English%20or%20France%20to%20the%20French.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20wrong%20and%20inhuman%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9Cto%20impose%20the%20Jews%20on%20the%20Arabs.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CSurely%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20sharply%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20would%20be%20a%20crime%20against%20humanity%20to%20reduce%20the%20proud%20Arabs%20so%20that%20Palestine%20can%20be%20restored%20to%20the%20Jews%20partly%20or%20wholly%20as%20their%20national%20home.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CThis%20cry%20for%20the%20national%20home%20affords%20a%20colourable%20justification%20for%20the%20German%20expulsion%20of%20the%20Jews.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENehru%20on%20June%2013%2C%201936%2C%20in%20a%20press%20statement%20on%20the%20April%201936%20revolt%20in%20Palestine%20against%20British%20imperialism%2C%20condemned%20it%20for%20creating%20a%20state%20for%20Jews%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20territory.%C2%A0%20He%20sympathised%20with%20the%20Jews%20and%20presciently%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20new%20state%20within%20a%20state%20was%20sought%20to%20be%20created%20in%20Palestine%2C%20an%20ever-growing%20state%20with%20the%20backing%20of%20British%20imperialism%20behind%20it%2C%20and%20the%20hope%20was%20held%20out%20that%20this%20new%20Jewish%20state%20would%2C%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20become%20so%20powerful%20in%20numbers%20and%20in%20economic%20position%20that%20it%20would%20dominate%20the%20whole%20of%20Palestine.%E2%80%9D%20According%20to%20him%2C%20the%20Arabs%20viewed%20it%20as%20British%20imperialism%E2%80%99s%20ploy%20to%20make%20the%20Arab-Jew%20problem%20a%20permanent%20obstacle%20to%20their%20independence.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20categorically%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20problem%20of%20Palestine%20is%20thus%20essentially%20a%20nationalist%20one%20%E2%80%94%20a%20people%20struggling%20for%20independence%20against%20imperialist%20control%20and%20exploitation%E2%80%A6%20It%20is%20not%20a%20racial%20or%20religious%20one.%E2%80%9D%20Observing%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CPerhaps%20some%20of%20our%20Muslim%20fellow%20countrymen%20extend%20their%20sympathy%20to%20the%20Arabs%20because%20of%20the%20religious%20bond%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20affirmed%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20Arabs%20are%20wiser%20and%20they%20lay%20stress%20only%20on%20nationalism%20and%20independence%2C%20and%20it%20is%20well%20to%20remember%20that%20all%20Arabs%2C%20Christian%20as%20well%20as%20Muslim%2C%20stand%20together%20in%20this%20struggle%20against%20British%20imperialism.%E2%80%9D%20He%20then%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20Jews%20had%20been%20wise%2C%20they%20would%20have%20thrown%20in%20their%20lot%20with%20the%20Arab%20struggle%20for%20independence.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CInstead%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20with%20anguish%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthey%20have%20chosen%20to%20side%20with%20British%20imperialism%20and%20to%20seek%20its%20protection%20against%20the%20people%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThose%20observations%20of%20Nehru%20assume%20significance%20in%20the%20context%20of%20some%20Hindutva%20forces%20distorting%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%20by%20employing%20Hindu-Muslim%20binaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20vision%20of%20Gandhi%20and%20Nehru%20shaped%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20guided%20our%20policy%20towards%20Israel%20and%20our%20support%20to%20the%20Palestine%20cause.%20India%20under%20Nehru%20voted%20against%20the%20partition%20of%20Palestine%20and%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20admission%20to%20the%20UN%20but%20recognised%20Israel%20in%201950%20after%20Turkey%20and%20Iran%20did%20so.%20Indira%20Gandhi%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20carried%20forward%20India%E2%80%99s%20solidarity%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20struggle%20and%20recognised%20the%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Organisation%20(PLO)%20as%20the%20sole%20legitimate%20representative%20of%20Palestine.%20She%20upgraded%20the%20PLO%20office%20in%20Delhi%20to%20that%20of%20an%20embassy%2C%20enjoying%C2%A0%20all%20diplomatic%20immunities%20and%20privileges.%20She%20forged%20strong%20ties%20with%20Yasser%20Arafat%20and%20in%20the%20NAM%20summit%20hosted%20by%20India%20in%201983%2C%20she%20reiterated%20that%20solidarity%20with%20Palestine.%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20continued%20that%20policy%20towards%20Palestine%2C%20and%20when%20the%20Palestinian%20intifada%20(uprising)%20began%C2%A0%20in%20December%201987%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20opposing%20the%20%E2%80%98iron%20fist%E2%80%99%20policies%20of%20Israel%2C%20India%20stood%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVajpayee%20as%20foreign%20minister%20during%20the%20Janata%20government%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Moraraji%20Desai%20upheld%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20Palestini