%3EHis%20latest%20property%20purchase%20adds%20to%20his%20extensive%20real-estate%20portfolio%20that%20includes%20two%20neighboring%20Beverly%20Hills%20mansions%20and%20a%20huge%20ranch%20in%20Texas%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-houses%5C%22%3EInsider's%20Sarah%20Jackson%20and%20Jordan%20Hart%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%20August.%20His%20home%20is%20a%2024%2C000-square-foot%20estate%20in%20Medina%2C%20Washington.%20He%20also%20owns%20a%20%24500%20million%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuperyacht-yacht-jeff-bezos-barry-diller-dvf-koru-eos-celebrity-2023-9%5C%22%3Esuperyacht%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20Koru.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiami-billionaire-bunker-private-island-tour-police-mansions-photos-2019-5%5C%22%3EIndian%20Creek%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20Bezos'%20new%20property%20purchase%20is%20located%2C%20is%20a%20village%20on%20a%20small%20private%20island%20in%20Miami's%20Biscayne%20Bay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0It%20was%20ranked%20by%20Zillow%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fresearch%2Fmillion-dollar-cities-2021-30655%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22321f4c3011b99bed21ba490a8ec65081%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fresearch%2Fmillion-dollar-cities-2021-30655%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22summary_bullets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20neighborhood%20in%20the%20US%20in%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20private%20island%20has%20stringent%20security%20measures%20and%20is%20heavily%20guarded%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-indian-creek-billionaire-bunker-miami-private-island-tour-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInsider's%20Hannah%20Towey%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0reported%20in%20December%202022%20after%20a%20tour%20of%20the%20area.%20Residents%20include%20Bezos%2C%20investor%20Carl%20Icahn%2C%20and%20Jared%20Kushner%20and%20Ivanka%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-buys-mansion-florida-miami-beach-billionaire-bunker-property-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697171767000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651f02e56e038039826a9565%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-buys-mansion-florida-miami-beach-billionaire-bunker-property-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bezos'%20latest%20purchase%20in%20the%20exclusive%20neighborhood%20is%20next%20to%20another%20property%20he%20had%20purchased%20this%20summer%20for%20%2468%20million.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22htan%40insider.com%20(Huileng%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-buys-mansion-florida-miami-beach-billionaire-bunker-property-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Ranks%20111th%20Among%20125%20Countries%20in%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13095335%2Fibrahim-rifath-xME0pKGyIro-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20has%20been%20ranked%20111%20among%20125%20countries%20in%20the%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%20report%20released%20by%20two%20European%20agencies%20on%20October%2012%2C%202023.%20India%20slipped%20four%20positions%20as%20compared%20to%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20countries%20ranking%20lower%20than%20India%20are%20Timor-Leste%2C%20Mozambique%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20Haiti%2C%20Guinea-Bissau%2C%20Liberia%2C%20Sierra%20Leone%2C%20Chad%2C%20Niger%2C%20Lesotho%2C%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo%2C%20Yemen%2C%20Madagascar%2C%20Central%20African%20Republic%2C%20South%20Sudan%2C%20Burundi%20and%20Somalia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20countries%2C%20which%20India%20has%20barely%20fared%20better%20than%2C%20are%20very%20small%20economies%20as%20compared%20to%20India.%20India%20is%20among%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldbank.org%2Fen%2Fcountry%2Findia%2Foverview%5C%22%3Efastest%20growing%20ones%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEvery%20other%20assessed%20country%2C%20besides%20these%20nations%2C%20had%20better%20outcomes%20than%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20stands%20in%20a%20group%20of%2040%20countries%20where%20the%20scale%20of%20global%20hunger%20has%20been%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%98serious%E2%80%99.%20The%20overall%20GHI%20score%20of%20India%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalhungerindex.org%2Fpdf%2Fen%2F2023.pdf%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%2C%2028.7.%20The%20calculation%20of%20this%20score%20is%20done%20on%20a%20100-point%20scale.%20The%20higher%20the%20score%2C%20the%20worse%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Concern%20Worldwide%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Welt%20Hungerhilfe%E2%80%99%2C%20two%20NGOs%20from%20Ireland%20and%20Germany%2C%20respectively%2C%20have%20come%20out%20with%20the%20report.%20According%20to%20the%20publishers%2C%20it%20is%20a%20peer-reviewed%20report%20which%20has%20been%20prepared%20annually%20from%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20high%20scores%20may%20be%20a%20symptom%20of%20several%20underlying%20problems%20relating%20to%20the%20nutritional%20status%20of%20the%20country.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20some%20countries%2C%20high%20scores%20are%20driven%20by%20high%20rates%20of%20undernourishment%2C%20reflecting%20a%20lack%20of%20calories%20for%20large%20swathes%20of%20the%20population%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFour%20factors%20were%20taken%20into%20account%20for%20calculating%20the%20GHI%20scores%3A%20undernourishment%20(refers%20to%20the%20entire%20population%20%E2%80%93%20both%20children%20and%20adults)%3B%20child%20stunting%20(share%20of%20children%20who%20have%20low%20height%20for%20their%20age)%3B%20child%20under-5%20mortality%3B%20and%20child%20wasting%20(children%20who%20have%20low%20weight%20for%20their%20height).%20All%20these%20indicators%20are%20components%20of%20the%20universally%20agreed%20UN%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20goes%20on%20to%20add%20that%20for%20some%20countries%2C%20a%20high%20GHI%20score%20may%20also%20reflect%20acute%20malnutrition%20among%20children%20and%20their%20poor%20nutrition%20levels%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20other%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%20challenges%20facing%20the%20population%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBroadly%20speaking%2C%20then%2C%20a%20high%20GHI%20score%20can%20be%20evidence%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20food%2C%20a%20poor-quality%20diet%2C%20inadequate%20child%20care-giving%20practices%2C%20an%20unhealthy%20environment%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20these%20factors%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20data%20sets%20presented%20in%20this%20report%20are%20secondary%20data%20and%20sourced%20from%20various%20published%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20performance%20on%20four%20parameters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20India%20has%20the%20highest%20child%20%E2%80%98wasting%E2%80%99%20(low%20weight%20for%20height)%20rate%20across%20the%20world%2C%20at%2018.7%25%2C%20reflecting%20acute%20undernutrition.%20In%20fact%2C%20%E2%80%98wasting%E2%80%99%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20worst%20form%20and%20indicator%20of%20all%20forms%20of%20child%20under-nutrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20country%20has%20more%20than%2015%25%20of%20the%20children%20%E2%80%98wasted%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20has%20been%20marked%20as%20%E2%80%98very%20high%E2%80%99%20level%20of%20concern%20in%20the%20report.%20India%20is%20the%20only%20country%2C%20thus%2C%20where%20the%20wasting%20has%20been%20put%20in%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98very%20high%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20childhood%20stunting%20(low%20height%20for%20age)%20goes%2C%20India%2C%20again%2C%20comes%20in%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98very%20high%E2%80%99%20risk%20countries.%20More%20than%2035%25%20children%20have%20been%20marked%20stunted%20in%20India%2C%20although%20several%20other%20African%20countries%20and%20some%20east-Asian%20countries%20perform%20worse%20than%20India%20on%20this%20parameter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Decadal%20Data%20Shows%20India%20Fails%20to%20Reduce%20Rate%20of%20Premature%20Births%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fin-previous-decade-india-could-not-reduce-rate-of-premature-births%5C%22%3EDecadal%20Data%20Shows%20India%20Fails%20to%20Reduce%20Rate%20of%20Premature%20Births%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20about%2016.6%25%20of%20the%20overall%20population%20undernourished%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20levels%20of%20undernourishment%20have%20been%20marked%20as%20of%20%E2%80%98medium%E2%80%99%20risk.%20And%2C%20in%20under-5%20mortality%2C%20India%20has%20been%20categorised%20as%20a%20country%20with%20%E2%80%98low%20risk%E2%80%99%2C%20with%20about%203.1%25%20of%20children%20dying%20before%20the%20age%20of%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20prevalence%20of%20anaemia%20among%20women%20aged%2015-24%20has%20been%20reported%20as%20a%20major%20problem%20for%20the%20country.%20More%20than%2050%25%20of%20women%20and%20adolescents%20are%20anaemic%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20objections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20has%20rejected%20this%20report%20this%20year%20too%2C%20like%20it%20has%20done%20on%20previous%20occasions.%20Issuing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetail.aspx%3FPRID%3D1967164%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20October%2012%2C%20the%20government%20has%20termed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalhungerindex.org%2Fmethodology.html%5C%22%3Emethodology%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20report%20preparation%20faulty%2C%20and%20has%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20four%20parameters%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThree%20out%20of%20the%20four%20indicators%20used%20for%20calculation%20of%20the%20index%20are%20related%20to%20the%20health%20of%20children%20and%20cannot%20be%20representative%20of%20the%20entire%20population%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20government%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fourth%20and%20most%20important%20indicator%20%E2%80%98Proportion%20of%20Undernourished%20(PoU)%20population%E2%80%99%20is%20based%20on%20an%20opinion%20poll%20conducted%20on%20a%20very%20small%20sample%20size%20of%203000%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20government%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20this%20data%20on%20%E2%80%98undernourishment%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20taken%20from%20the%20State%20of%20Food%20Security%20and%20Nutrition%20in%20the%20World%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fao.org%2F3%2Fcc3017en%2Fcc3017en.pdf%5C%22%3ESOFI%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20prepared%20by%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Food%20and%20Agriculture%20Organisation%20(FAO)%2C%20United%20Nations%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Fund%20and%20International%20Fund%20(UNICEF)%20and%20International%20Fund%20for%C2%A0%20Agricultural%20Development%20(IFAD).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20SOFI%20report%2C%20the%20data%20on%20food%20insecurity%20since%202014%20has%20been%20collected%20in%20more%20than%20140%20countries%2C%20through%20a%20private%20polling%20agency%20which%20would%20ask%20eight%20questions%20to%20the%20respondents.%20While%20in%20most%20countries%201%2C000%20such%20interviews%20were%20conducted%2C%20for%20India%20the%20respective%20sample%20size%20was%20larger%20%E2%80%93%203%2C000%20%E2%80%93%20a%20figure%20though%20the%20Indian%20government%20berated%20in%20its%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20also%20cast%20doubts%20over%20using%20stunting%20and%20wasting%20as%20two%20indicators%20for%20the%20GHI%20report%20preparation.%20The%20government%20says%20%E2%80%98hunger%E2%80%99%20may%20cause%20stunting%20and%20wasting%2C%20but%20they%20could%20also%20be%20a%20result%20of%20factors%20like%20sanitation%2C%20genetics%2C%20utilisation%20of%20food%20intake%20etc.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20raised%20questions%20over%20using%20%E2%80%98hunger%E2%80%99%20as%20something%20it%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%98causative%2Foutcome%E2%80%99%20for%20stunting%20and%20wasting%2C%20for%20the%20GHI%20scores.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20of%20India%20also%20went%20on%20to%20make%20a%20rather%20unusual%20claim%3A%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20hardly%20any%20evidence%20that%20the%20fourth%20indicator%2C%20namely%2C%20child%20mortality%20is%20an%20outcome%20of%20hunger%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%20There%20is%20though%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20hunger%20does%20lead%20to%20death%20in%20children%20in%20many%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMalnourished%20children%2C%20particularly%20those%20with%20severe%20acute%20malnutrition%2C%20have%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20death%20from%20common%20childhood%20illnesses%20such%20as%20diarrhoea%2C%20pneumonia%20and%20malaria.%20Nutrition-related%20factors%20contribute%20to%20about%2045%25%20of%20deaths%20in%20children%20under%205%20years%20of%20age%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Flevels-and-trends-in-child-under-5-mortality-in-2020%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMalnourished%2520children%252C%2520particularly%2520those%2520with%2Cunder%25205%2520years%2520of%2520age.%5C%22%3EWorld%20Health%20Organisation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20also%20contested%20the%20childhood%20wasting%20figures%20of%20India.%20It%20said%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98poshan%E2%80%99%20tracker%20said%207.3%25%20of%20the%20children%20were%20%E2%80%98wasted%E2%80%99%20as%20against%20GHI%20figures%20of%2018.7%25.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.unicef.org%2Fresources%2Fjme-report-2023%2F%5C%22%3Einter-agency%20UN%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehad%20estimated%20the%20prevalence%20of%20wasting%20at%2018.7%25%20%E2%80%93%20the%20source%20of%20GHI%E2%80%99s%20wasting%20rate%20for%20India.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20(NFHS)-5%20data%20for%202019-21%20had%20said%20the%20corresponding%20figure%20was%2019.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20reports%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20GHI%20report%20is%20not%20an%20outlier%20to%20point%20out%20India%E2%80%99s%20poor%20performance%20in%20nutrition.%20The%20SOFI%20reports%20have%20done%20so%20consistently%20over%20the%20past.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fao.org%2F3%2Fcc3017en%2Fcc3017en.pdf%5C%22%3ESOFI-2023%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20pointed%20out%20that%2074.1%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20population%20is%20unable%20to%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet.%20Only%20countries%20like%20Nepal%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Sierra%20Leone%2C%20Nigeria%2C%20Niger%2C%20Burkina-Faso%2C%20Ghana%2C%20Liberia%2C%20Guinea%20and%20Guinea%20Bissau%20had%20a%20higher%20share%20of%20their%20respective%20populations%20than%20India%20which%20were%20not%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20SOFI-2023%20report%20also%20said%20233.9%20million%20(24%20crore)%20people%20in%20India%20are%20%E2%80%98undernourished%E2%80%99.%20Undernourishment%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SOFI%20report%2C%20is%20defined%20as%20the%20condition%20of%20an%20individual%20whose%20habitual%20food%20consumption%20is%20insufficient%20to%20provide%2C%20on%20average%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20dietary%20energy%20required%20to%20maintain%20a%20normal%2C%20active%20and%20healthy%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20written%20to%20the%20two%20agencies%20which%20have%20prepared%20the%20GHI%20report%20seeking%20their%20response%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20objections.%20Their%20replied%20will%20be%20added%20when%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697171308000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13095335%2Fibrahim-rifath-xME0pKGyIro-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Findia-ranks-111th-among-125-countries-in-global-hunger-index-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20only%20countries%20which%20got%20worse%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%20scores%20than%20India%20are%20Timor-Leste%2C%20Mozambique%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20Haiti%2C%20Guinea-Bissau%2C%20Liberia%2C%20Sierra%20Leone%2C%20Chad%2C%20Niger%2C%20Lesotho%2C%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo%2C%20Yemen%2C%20Madagascar%2C%20Central%20African%20Republic%2C%20South%20Sudan%2C%20Burundi%20and%20Somalia.%20India%20has%20rejected%20the%20findings%2C%20saying%20the%20methodology%20is%20faulty.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Findia-ranks-111th-among-125-countries-in-global-hunger-index-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UN%20Warns%20of%20%E2%80%98Devastating%20Humanitarian%20Consequences%E2%80%99%20as%20Israel%20Gives%20All%20Palestinians%2024%20Hours%20to%20Leave%20North%20Gaza%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13095608%2Fimage1170x530cropped.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20army%20has%20said%20that%20all%20the%20people%20living%20in%20northern%20Gaza%20must%20move%20to%20the%20southern%20region%20within%20the%20next%2024%20hours%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20has%20said.%20This%20indicates%20that%20a%20massive%20ground%20invasion%20may%20be%20on%20the%20cards.%3C%