0medium%20where%20there's%20only%20room%20for%20the%20most%20brief%2C%20emotional%2C%20visceral%20reaction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDagnes%20said%20the%20nature%20of%20social%20media%20and%20the%20attention%20economy%20means%20that%20there%20is%20a%20financial%20incentive%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20platforms%20to%20keep%20users%20scrolling%2C%20clicking%2C%20commenting.%20And%20it's%20often%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fhow-tech-platforms-fuel-u-s-political-polarization-and-what-government-can-do-about-it%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtroversial%2C%20hot%20takes%20that%20get%20higher%20engagement%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20therefore%20get%20shared%20or%20served%20up%20to%20more%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20much%20easier%2C%20and%20emotionally%20appealing%2C%20to%20clearly%20define%20the%20good%20guys%20and%20the%20bad%20guys%20and%20leave%20it%20at%20that%2C%20she%20said.%20But%20that's%20exactly%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrying%20to%20explain%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20in%20one%20picture%20is%20almost%20like%20a%20Second%20City%20sketch.%20It's%20like%20'Name%20That%20Tune%2C'%20but%20with%20one%20note.%20You%20can't%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20impossible%20task%2C%20to%20take%20something%20so%20nuanced%20and%20so%20complicated%20and%20turn%20it%20into%20something%20that's%20simple%20enough%20to%20digest%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stuff%20that's%20good%20and%20real%20and%20thoughtful%20is%20boring%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPolarization%20and%20misinformation%20are%20common%20on%20social%20media%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKen%20Paulson%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Free%20Speech%20Center%20at%20Middle%20Tennessee%20State%20University%2C%20agreed%20that%20social%20media%20does%20not%20lend%20itself%20to%20useful%20conversations%20on%20the%20broader%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conf