%80%99s%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%202023.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20city%20of%20Ahmedabad%2C%20the%20nerve%20centre%20of%20Hindu-Muslim%20politics%2C%20gets%20ready%20to%20host%20Pakistan%20for%20a%20World%20Cup%20encounter%2C%20I%20am%20reminded%20of%20Zardar%20Khan.%20While%20I%20imagine%2C%20with%20apprehension%2C%20a%20mass%20of%20humanity%20(one%20lakh%20thirty%20thousand)%20watching%20the%20match%20at%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20stadium%20and%20wonder%20what%20fate%20awaits%20us%2C%20my%20mind%20races%20back%20in%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20think%20of%20the%20complex%20India-Pakistan%20relationship%2C%20symbolised%20by%20a%20very%20passionate%20and%20turbulent%20cricketing%20rivalry%20dotted%20by%20many%20memorable%20moments%2C%20this%20tall%2C%20young%2C%20fair%20Pathan%20from%20Pakistan%20flashes%20through%20my%20mind.%20Young%20he%20no%20longer%20can%20be.%20Nearly%2025%20years%20have%20passed%20since%20a%20bunch%20of%20cricket%20writers%20met%20him%20in%20London%20during%20the%201999%20World%20Cup%2C%20which%20England%20was%20hosting%20for%20the%20fourth%20time.%20Zardar%20was%20a%20taxi%20driver%20by%20profession%2C%20like%20thousands%20of%20Indians%20and%20Pakistanis%20living%20in%20the%20country%20of%20their%20former%20colonial%20masters%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20a%20proud%2C%20patriotic%20Pakistani%20who%20believed%20his%20country%20to%20be%20no%20less%20strong%2C%20cultured%20and%20civilised%20than%20India.%20There%20were%20many%20moments%20during%20our%20interaction%20when%20I%20felt%20he%20even%20believed%20his%20country%20to%20be%20superior%20to%20his%20neighbours%E2%80%99%2C%20torn%20apart%20during%20the%20horrific%20partition%20in%201947.%20Professional%20needs%20had%20tempered%20his%20conduct%20and%20he%20was%20more%20respectful%20of%20us%20than%20he%20may%20have%20liked%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20ferried%20us%20in%20his%20taxi%20in%20London%20and%20many%20other%20match%20venues%2C%20we%20became%20friends.%20It%20was%2C%20perhaps%2C%20the%20best%20and%20the%20worst%20of%20times%20for%20the%20citizens%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20to%20befriend%20each%20other.%20The%20Kargil%20battle%20was%20at%20our%20doorsteps%20and%2C%20with%20each%20passing%20second%2C%20even%20threatening%20to%20engulf%20the%20two%20nations%20into%20a%20full-blown%20war.%20War%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cricketcountry.com%2Farticles%2Fworld-cup-1999-india-and-pakistan-put-aside-kargil-to-battle-on-field-246287%5C%22%3Ethreatening%20to%20disrupt%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20India-Pakistan%20World%20Cup%20clash%2C%20scheduled%20for%20June%208%20at%20Old%20Trafford%20in%20Manchester.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThose%20on%20the%20extreme%20right%20felt%20it%20was%20madness%20to%20play%20cricket%20with%20Pakistan%20when%20their%20army%20had%20engineered%20the%20war%20and%20killed%20our%20soldiers.%20The%20World%20Cup%20organisers%20feared%20violent%20clashes%20between%20the%20thousands%20of%20expats%20from%20the%20two%20nations%20who%20were%20going%20to%20fill%20the%20stadium.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EZardar%20had%20driven%20us%20to%20Manchester%20and%20he%20firmly%20believed%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20was%20in%20full%20control%20of%20the%20war%20and%20would%20emerge%20victorious.%20Somehow%2C%20and%20I%20would%20say%20it%20was%20the%20miracle%20of%20cricket%20and%20sports%2C%20the%20journalists%20from%20India%20and%20Zardar%20were%20still%20friends%20and%20were%20discussing%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20the%20match%20more%20than%20the%20war.%20Cricket%20had%20led%20to%20the%20forging%20of%20a%20bond%20which%20could%20transcend%20the%20negative%20baggage%20of%20a%20bitter%20past%20and%20rigid%20national%20boundaries.%20We%20could%20see%20in%20each%20other%20qualities%20and%20vulnerabilities%20common%20to%20all%20human%20beings.%20The%20very%20idea%20of%20the%20match%20getting%20cancelled%20was%20unacceptable%20to%20a%20cricket%20fan%2C%20no%20matter%20with%20which%20country%20his%20loyalty%20lay.%20Unlike%20war%2C%20which%20produces%20dead%20bodies%2C%20cricket%20produces%20harmless%20fours%20and%20sixes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fz0vUNTQcL48%3Fsi%3Dp3UjpFjeUpnOTQVa%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20manifestation%20of%20camaraderie%20and%20friendship%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20travel%20to%20the%20ground%20in%20Zardar%E2%80%99s%20taxi%20with%20the%20flags%20of%20both%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20hoisted%20on%20the%20bonnet%20of%20the%20car.%20On%20the%20neutral%20territory%20of%20England%2C%20the%20two%20national%20flags%20adjacent%20to%20each%20other%2C%20unlike%20the%20hundreds%20that%20were%20waved%20that%20day%20inside%20and%20outside%20the%20ground%2C%20pleaded%20for%20peace%20and%20togetherness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20have%20not%20been%20in%20touch%20with%20Zardar%20since%20the%201999%20World%20Cup.%20What%20would%20he%20make%20of%202023%20and%20the%20literal%20collapse%20of%20his%20own%20country%2C%20in%20economic%20and%20even%20cricketing%20terms%3F%20Unlike%20the%20fierce%2C%20determined%20and%20ferociously%20competitive%20Pakistani%20teams%20from%20the%20past%2C%20the%20current%20one%20seems%20in%20awe%20of%20the%20Indians.%20As%20someone%20put%20it%2C%20they%20treat%20their%20Indian%20counterparts%20with%20too%20much%20respect%20and%20seem%20even%20apologetic%20that%20they%20have%20to%20compete%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20formidable%20Indians%2C%20without%20doubt%20the%20favourites%20to%20win%20not%20only%20the%20Ahmedabad%20match%20but%20the%20World%20Cup%20itself%2C%20have%20multiplied%20their%20fanbase%20in%20India.%20They%20believe%20their%20team%20is%20invincible%20and%20this%20Pakistan%20team%20is%20like%20a%20sacrificial%20lamb%2C%20with%20Ahmedabad%20being%20the%20chosen%20venue.%20The%20thought%20of%20defeat%20never%20even%20brushes%20their%20mind.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20can%20never%20lose%2C%20%3Cem%3Ethat%20too%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20emphasis%20on%20Ahmedabad%20is%20very%20pronounced%20from%20this%20Indian%20fan%20when%20I%20seek%20his%20reaction%20to%20a%20possible%20Indian%20defeat.%20It%20is%20a%20city%20synonymous%20with%20Modi%20and%20it%20is%20obvious%20this%20invincibility%20flows%20down%20from%20their%20beloved%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20replace%20Zardar%20Khan%20in%20my%20imagination%20with%20the%20lone%20Pakistani%2C%20Mohammad%20Bashir%2C%20who%20is%20in%20India%20supporting%20his%20team.%20Pakistani%20journalists%20and%20citizens%20have%20not%20been%20issued%20visas%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20so%20far.%20Bashir%20was%20because%20he%20is%20an%20American%20passport%20holder.%20He%20has%20been%20to%20every%20World%20Cup%20since%202007%20and%20I%20visualise%20him%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%20heading%20towards%20the%20stadium%20to%20watch%20the%20match.%20If%20he%20is%20very%20observant%20and%20aware%20of%20history%2C%20he%20would%20be%20very%20pleased%20to%20spot%20the%20emblem%20of%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Management%20(IIM)%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20sporting%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstylized%20representation%20of%20an%20exquisitely%20crafted%20sandstone%20lattice%20(zali)%20window%E2%80%9D%20that%20is%20taken%20from%20the%20design%20of%20the%20Sidi%20Saiyyed%20mosque%20built%20in%20the%2016th%20century.%20What%20would%20thrill%20him%20even%20more%20is%20when%20he%20realises%20that%20Ahmedabad%20was%20built%20by%20a%20Muslim%20ruler%2C%20Ahmed%20Shah%2C%20in%20the%2015th%20century%20and%20its%20name%20has%20not%20been%20changed%20by%20a%20government%20which%20abhors%20all%20Muslim%20rulers%20of%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20would%20be%20hard%20for%20him%20to%20comprehend%20is%20that%20in%20the%20Gujarati%20subconscious%2C%20the%20name%20of%20their%20city%20is%20not%20to%20be%20confused%20with%20Ahmed%20Shah.%20They%20call%20it%20Amdavad.%20It%20might%20be%20even%20harder%20for%20him%20to%20comprehend%20that%20in%20a%20stadium%20hosting%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20supporters%20in%20the%20history%20of%20this%20sport%2C%20there%20may%20not%20be%20a%20single%20spectator%20showing%20his%20affinity%20for%20the%20Pakistan%20team.%20If%20there%20are%20some%2C%20like%20there%20were%20many%20rooting%20for%20Pakistan%20when%20they%20played%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20they%20better%20remain%20silent.%20I%20am%20not%20sure%20if%20it%20would%20be%20prudent%20for%20him%20to%20walk%20to%20the%20venue%20holding%20the%20Pakistani%20flag%20and%20wave%20it%20inside%20the%20stadium%2C%20as%20his%20safety%20and%20security%20could%20be%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPradeep%20Magazine%20is%20a%20cricket%20writer%20and%20the%20author%20of%20two%20books%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20Not%20Quite%20Cricket%20%3Cem%3Eand%20the%20recently%20published%3C%2Fem%3E%20Not%20Just%20Cricket%2C%20A%20Reporter%E2%80%99s%20Journey%20Through%20Modern%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697126448000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F27090351%2FScreen-Shot-2021-10-27-at-9.02.35-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Findia-pakistan-cricket-on-a-sticky-wicket-in-ahmedabad%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mohammad%20Bashir%20is%20the%20lone%20Pakistani%20in%20India%20supporting%20his%20team.%20Unlike%20Pakistani%20journalists%20and%20citizens%2C%20who%20have%20not%20been%20issued%20visas%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20so%20far%2C%20he%20got%20his%20visa%20for%20India%20because%20he%20is%20an%20American%20passport%20holder.%20He%20has%20been%20to%20every%20World%20Cup%20since%202007.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Findia-pakistan-cricket-on-a-sticky-wicket-in-ahmedabad%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%